The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '1.0.0' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pybcj" %}
{% set version = "1.0.1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8b682ed08caabfb7c042d4be083e28ddc692afb1deff5567111f8855071b75c3

build:
  number: 2
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools >=42.0
    - setuptools-scm >=3.5.0
  run:
    - importlib-metadata  # [py<38]
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - bcj
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://github.com/miurahr/pybcj
  summary: bcj filter library
  license: LGPL-2.1-or-later
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sarthakpati
